ture at the time. Courting Celebrity illustrates women’s practice in two key literary genres, poetry and autobiography, and illuminates the strategies of women’s self-fashioning and pursuit of celebrity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAutobiographieszItaly. 0aWomen poets, Italiany19th centuryvBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aAglaja Anassillide.  aAngela Veronese.  aItalian literature.  aTeresa Bandettini.  aVenice and Venetian culture.  aautobiography.  acelebrity.  agardens.  apastoral poetry.  apoet-improviser.  asalons.  asociability.  awomen’s writing.1 aWard, Adrienne , econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWard, Adrienne , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZanini-Cordi, Irene , econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZanini-Cordi, Irene , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754642740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487546427423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487546427/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK